title: Oct. 10: SUNY New Paltz roundup
text: Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 11:22 PM Updated at 11:26 PM Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 11:22 PM Updated at 11:26 PM Women’s tennis New Paltz 5, Brockport 0 SUNY New Paltz: Hawks (6-2) advance to Sunday’s SUNYAC final against defending champion SUNY Geneseo (10 a.m.); New Paltz swept 3 doubles matches; Brittany Grandville and Carol Tyson post straight-set singles wins. Women's soccer New Paltz 0, Potsdam 0 (2 OT) SUNY New Paltz: Hawks move to 2-10-2 (1-3-2 SUNYAC); Mikaela Stiklickas 4 saves. Men's soccer New Paltz 4, Potsdam 3 SUNY New Paltz: Hawks improve to 9-5 (3-2 SUNYAC); goals by Jason Gonzalez (13th, 30th minutes), Tyler Lundgren (55th) and Jake Falk (74th); John Guzzo 4 saves on 7 shots. Women's volleball New Paltz 3, Plattsburgh 1 SUNY New Paltz: Hawks prevail 25-19, 22-25, 25-12, 25-20; Becca Borquist 17 kills, 18 digs; Maddie Zwickl 51 assists; Rachel Pierson 29 digs; Morgan Roessler 6 blocks. New Paltz 3, Buffalo State 1 SUNY New Paltz: Hawks (14-7, 6-0 SUNYAC) prevail 25-23, 22-25, 25-21, 25-17; Morgan Roessler 14 kills; Becca Borquist 14 kills, 16 digs; Maddie Zwickl 49 assists, 11 digs; Rache; Pierson 34 digs. Women's field hockey William Smith 4, New Paltz 1 SUNY New Paltz: 19th ranked Hawks fall to 10-3; Sam Eberle scored in 34th minute; Alayna Wageman and Megan Gangewere combined for 4 saves. recordonline.com Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 11:22 PM Updated at 11:26 PM
